title: Alpe Named #ASunWGolf Co-Player of the Week
text: Emelie Alpe & Stetson's Kristine Odaiyar tied at the Jacksonville Classic in sixth place with identical rounds and in the process shared the Atlantic Sun Women's Golfer of the Week award, announced Thursday by the league office.Alpe guided the Ospreys to a third-place team finish with rounds of 71-74-71 at the Marsh Landing Country Club in Pone Vedra Beach, Fla. Her two under-par rounds increased UNF's program record to seven, while she tallied 10 birdies in the three rounds including six in her final round. The honor marks the third of her career and second this season."Emelie continues to play at a very high level," said UNF head coach . "She challenges herself each week and has a strong commitment to be successful. We are very proud of her accomplishments on the course."Alpe and her Osprey teammates next compete Oct. 12-13 at the Pinehurst Challenge in PInehurst, N.C. Atlantic Sun Women's Co-Golfer of the Week - Oct. 1st
